original: Karlsson, Karl-Fredrik, veterinär, Linköping, f. 10/3/131 i V. Husby, Ös-tergötl. k, av Johan Fredrik K. o. Hilda Dahlgren. G. 37 m. Birgit Kar-nock. Barn: Lars f. 37, Anders 44. — Studiex. i Norrköp. 32, veter:ex. i Sthlim 43’, stud. v. Sthdfms högsk. o. Upps. univ. 313’. Kort. förordn. s. tf. distr:veter. 39-46, assist: ve ter. v. stat. veter :med. anist. 42-45, v. Östergötd. 1. hush:sällsk. fr. 45. Skr.: upps. i Skand. veter :tidskr. (45-46). Hoibby: faunis-tiska stud.
translated: Karlsson, Karl-Fredrik, veterinarian, Linköping, b. 10/3/1913 in V. Husby, Östergötland county, son of Johan Fredrik K. and Hilda Dahlgren. Married in 1937 to Birgit Karnock. Children: Lars, born in 1937, Anders, born in 1944. Completed studies in Norrköping in 1932, obtained a veterinary degree in Stockholm in 1943, studied at Stockholm's College of Veterinary Medicine and Uppsala University from 1931 to 1933. Held temporary positions as district veterinarian from 1939 to 1946, assistant veterinarian at the state veterinary medical institute from 1942 to 1945, and at Östergötland County household company from 1945. Published articles in the Scandinavian Veterinary Journal from 1945 to 1946. Hobby: faunistic studies.
